OL,3,CThe reason why Reform UK chose to
OL,4,Claunch its 'contract' in Wales
OL,6,FMore than four thousand people joined
OL,7,Fthe party on Monday June 3 alone - the
OL,8,Fday Mr Farage announced his decision
OL,9,Fto become party leader and stand in
OL,10,Fthe general election.
OL,12,FResponding to Reform's Manifesto
OL,13,Flaunch, Welsh Labour's campaign chair,
OL,14,FJessica Morden, said: "Nigel Farage's
OL,15,Fbrand of divisive politics is not
OL,16,Fwelcome here in Wales.
OL,18,F"Wales has a proud history of being an
OL,19,Finclusive society, and Reform's band
OL,20,Fof chancers seeking to sow division
OL,21,Fwill find little succour.
